post_text:
We have delivered the supplies to the Glenville-Emmons School!
Items that were delivered:
-backpacks
-notebooks/folders/composition notebooks
-pens/pencils
-crayons/colored pencils
-markers/highlighters/dry erase markers
-glue/glue sticks
-rulers
-scissors
-pencil boxes/pencil holders
-erasers
-masks
-hand sanitizer
-kleenex
And many, many various items and cash we collected! I did not get total counts because the amount of supplies was overwhelming! The cash that was collected will be used to cover costs for fans that will be used in the classrooms. All in all, we had a truck load of boxes, 15 large to mid-sized boxes full of supplies for the Glenville-Emmons school district. It… More

post_text:
💙We turn on the lights of Glenville-Emmons football field for you tonight, students! Just a small gesture to remind all of our students and communities that they are still in our thoughts.

🤍These lights represent faith that life will return to normal soon! We will fill our hallways and classrooms again and we can’t wait to see you again! In honor of you, we will light up our field for you 8:00 to 9:00 pm.

💙We ask that you enjoy the lights from afar as to make sure we are all doing our part to honor social distancing and stay safe. #BeTheLightMN

This summer we unexpectedly lost a member of the Glenville-Emmons family. Jim Smith was a para at the high school, SPED van driver, the JV softball coach, an avid football fan, and a dedicated member of the Glenville Fire Department. To honor his memory, we are dedicating this school year to him and have created t-shirts.

Shirts can be purchased at the following link. Deadline for purchasing is Aug. 27, and shirts will be able to be picked up at the high school on Friday Sept. 7.

Please direct any questions to Elise Volz at volze@geschools.com

http://squareup.com/store/coachsmith

post_text: The first graders enjoyed a field trip to Mayo Clinic Health Systems in Albert Lea on Tuesday. They learned about the body, what it would be like to be a patient, and took a tour of the hospital. They saw blood cells through a microscope, a short stay surgical room, an ambulance, and even a brand new baby!

post_text:
The Rotary Club in Albert Lea has filled the "Glenville Little Library" with books. The Little Library is located on the south side of the Elementary by the Preschool door. The idea is for people to take a book to read, and return it when they have finished reading it. People can also bring one of their own books to share. The Rotary Club made the structure and donated a Little Library to every school in Freeborn County. The custodial staff put the structure up this summer. The GE art department will be decorating the Little Library this fall.
Pictured: Weston, Avery, Kennedy, Mrs. Haugh

PLEASE SHARE/FORWARD to anyone you think maybe interested:

The filing affidavits for the office of school board member of ID No. 2886 end today (8/16/16). Term is for 4 years. A candidate for this office must be an eligible voter, 21 years of age or more on assuming office, must have been a resident of ID No. 2886, and must have no other affidavit on file for any other office at the same time as the general election.

If you have questions, please contact Jarred Anderson at the high school office or Lisa Hajek.
